post_cb({"35346617": {"ParentId": "35344795", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>The type either has linkage, or it doesn't. This paragraph is self-contained: the first half defines the notion of a type having linkage, and the second half describes restrictions on the use of types having no linkage. The notion of linkage of a type is not used anywhere else, as far as I can tell.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1670129", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "35346617", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2016-02-11T17:54:43.930", "LastActivityDate": "2016-02-11T17:54:43.930"}, "35344795": {"CommentCount": "0", "ViewCount": "55", "CreationDate": "2016-02-11T16:28:38.820", "LastActivityDate": "2016-02-11T17:54:43.930", "Title": "Does a type just have 'linkage' other than internal/external linkage?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "35346617", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "35344795", "Score": "1", "Body": "<p>3.5 [basic.link] paragraph 8 from <em>N4567</em> says that</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_35344795_35344795_0\">... A type is said to have <strong>linkage</strong> if and only if:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>it is a class or enumeration type that is named (or has a name for linkage purposes (7.1.3)) and the name has linkage; or</li>\n<li>...</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n<p>which exclusively elaborates on linkage of types\u2014one of the entities that a name can denote. However, it seems that <strong>there is no information in this paragraph whether the linkage that a type shall have is internal or external</strong>. Is it because there is no need to define it at all, or because it is already defined by other paragraphs?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><language-lawyer><linkage>", "OwnerUserId": "5645940", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_35344795_35344795_0": {"section_id": 7141, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}}, "n3337": {"so_35344795_35344795_0": {"section_id": 6885, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}}, "n4659": {"so_35344795_35344795_0": {"section_id": 8642, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}}}});